achatina.name: Achatina(玛瑙螺)
achatina.desc: The Achatina is a massive snail, mostly used for its production of Cementing Paste, or as a pet. This creature produces its paste passively — and quite frequently — so many survivors keep them around their bases. However, its usefulness pretty much ends there, as it cannot attack and moves quite slow. The Achatina must be tamed violently.

allosaurus.name: Allosaurus
allosaurus.desc: The Allosaurus is a pack-hunting theropod that's smaller but faster than Rex, and larger but slower than Carnotaurus. When in packs of 3 or more, the highest level Allosaurus will become the pack leader, emitting a red aura and making it stronger in battle.

ammonite.name: Ammonite
ammonite.desc: While the Ammonite cannot be tamed, it is often hunted as its bile can be used to make powerful antidotes.

archaeopteryx.name: Archaeopteryx
archaeopteryx.desc: The Archaeopteryx is a tree-dwelling bird-like dinosaur. While its smaller frame make it unfit for riding, it is strong enough to carry humans, allowing them to glide across long distances. Taming an Archaeopteryx is no simple task, as it will immediately flee when approached, and once knocked out, it prefers to eat rare insect matter.

attackdrone.name: Attack Drone
attackdrone.tamingNotice: This creature's Dododex profile may contain spoilers. Have a good strategy on how to battle the Attack Drone? Share a tip!

baryonyx.name: Baryonyx
baryonyx.desc: The Baryonyx is a large crocodile-like predator. While it might lack in attack power, its ability to swim extremtly fast makes it a fierce opponent — especially with its ability to travel on both land and in water.

basilisk.name: Basilisk
basilisk.desc: The Basilisk is a fearsome snake-like creature in Ark: Aberration.
basilisk.tamingNotice: To tame a Basilisk, you must feed it fertilized eggs.

basilosaurus.name: Basilosaurus
basilosaurus.desc: The Basilosaurus is a dolphin-like creature that primarily dwells along the shallow areas of the ocean. It has the ability to keep survivors warm or cool.

beelzebufo.name: Beelzebufo
beelzebufo.desc: One of the island's most useful amphibians, the beelzebufo can create cementing paste in its stomach simply by eating insects. Incredibly fast when hopping, its jumps can traverse vast expanses at the cost of little to no stamina. The beelzebufo can swim especially well and is one of the few creatures that can cause torpor using its attack. While it may be a little difficult to tame safely, many survivors consider it an especially useful addition to their tribes.

bulbdog.name: Bulbdog
bulbdog.desc: The Bulbdog (originally referred to as a 'Lantern Pug') is a cute bulldog-like creature in Ark: Aberration with a glowing orb antenna. The Bulbdog can be carried on a human's shoulder. It is a passive tame.

brontosaurus.name: Brontosaurus
brontosaurus.desc: The Brontosaurus is a behemoth of a dinosaur with a powerful tail 'tail sweep' attack that can smash all nearby enemies. This method is also one of the most efficient ways to gather berries and thatch, and the Brontosaurus' ability to carry large quantities of items make it even more useful for gathering. With its ability to carry a Platform Saddle, the Brontosaurus is often considered a must-have dinosaur for nomadic tribes looking for a mobile base.

broodmotherlysrix.name: Broodmother Lysrix
broodmotherlysrix.tamingNotice: The Broodmother Lysrix is one of the three bosses. Have a good strategy on how to battle Broodmother Lysrix? Share a tip!

chalicotherium.name: Chalicotherium
chalicotherium.desc: The Chalicotherium is a mammal commonly found in colder areas that many survivors find useful in battle. In the wild, Chalicotherium often playfully throw snowballs and mud rocks at each other, however, when tamed, they can be given boulders to throw at enemy structures.

cnidaria.name: Cnidaria
cnidaria.desc: The Cnidaria is a small jellyfish found in the deepest depths of the oceans. This easy-to-spot creature won't attack unless approached too closely. It delivers a sedative sting that can knock out enemies if striked repeatedly. While it cannot be tamed, survivors will hunt it to gather its sedative, which is used for advanced tranquilizers.

coelacanth.name: Coelacanth
coelacanth.tamingNotice: The Coelacanth can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

daeodon.name: Daeodon
daeodon.desc: The Daeodon (or 'Hell Pig') is a vicious pig. This pig has a high healing and food consumption rate, making it difficult to maintain. It can be tamed and ridden, however, taming it is quite a difficult task.

deathworm.name: Deathworm
deathworm.tamingNotice: The Deathworm is not tamable. It can be found in the outer deserts of Scorched Earth. Have a good strategy on how to battle it? Share a tip!

defenseunit.name: Defense Unit
defenseunit.tamingNotice: This creature's Dododex profile may contain spoilers. Have a good strategy on how to battle the Defense Unit? Share a tip!

dilophosaur.name: Dilophosaur
dilophosaur.desc: A Dilophosaur is a small, relatively weak dinosaur. Still, they're easy to tame for newer survivors, and are not hard to manage. They serve as guard dogs or pack-hunters, but are easily killed. Don't get too attached to them, as they likely won't survive combat against stronger dinosaurs.

diplocaulus.name: Diplocaulus
diplocaulus.desc: The Diplocaulus is a swamp amphibian with one major use once tamed; becoming a living oxygen bag. When swimming to the depths of the ocean, some disgusting survivors will suck on the bladders of a tamed diplocaulus' head as an effective oxygen source.

diplodocus.name: Diplodocus
diplodocus.desc: The Diplodocus is a smaller sauropod best known for its ten-person (plus one driver) saddle, making it an excellent dino for group transport.

doedicurus.name: Doedicurus
doedicurus.desc: Note: The Doedicurus can gather Obsidian from a small number of rocks, such as the ones on the volcano on The Island. It cannot gather Obsidian from most usual Obsidian rocks.

dragon.name: Dragon
dragon.tamingNotice: The Dragon is one of the three bosses. Have a good strategy on how to battle Dragon? Share a tip!

electrophorus.name: Electrophorus
electrophorus.desc: The Electrophorus is an electric eel with the ability to shock its targets.

equus.name: Equus
equus.tamingNotice: To tame the Equus, you must mount it immediately after the first feeding. Tap the action button each time you're prompted to feed again.
equus.desc: The Equus is a horse-like creature that can be mounted with special saddles. While mounted, survivors can use whips and lassos.

eurypterid.name: Eurypterid
eurypterid.tamingNotice: The Eurypterid is not tamable. It can be found on the bottom of the ocean floor.

featherlight.name: Featherlight
featherlight.desc: The Featherlight is a tamable bird-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

gallimimus.name: Gallimimus
gallimimus.desc: The Gallimimus is extremely fragile, but its power to outrun everything gained place in the hearts of survivors who look for a mount to explore and scout the island by land, or just want to evade battle. This creature is unable to harvest most resources or attack enemy, but its reputation as fastest creature sure make it a valuable mount.

giantbee.name: Giant Bee
giantbee.desc: The Giant Bee builds its nest at the tops of Redwood trees. While it's not an easy task, a nest can be broken open and the queen can be tamed. Once tamed, she will generate honey as well as lay drone eggs.
giantbee.tamingNotice: To tame a Queen Giant Bee, you must first destroy her nest. The nest has 5,000 health.

glowbug.name: Glowbug
glowbug.tamingNotice: The Glowbug is a firefly-like creature in Ark: Aberration.
glowbug.desc: The Glowbug is a firefly-like creature in Ark: Aberration. Creatures with charges can extract a charge from Glowbugs. They can be found in all biomes other than the surface.

glowtail.name: Glowtail
glowtail.tamingNotice: The Glowtail is a lizard-like creature in Ark: Aberration.
glowtail.desc: The Glowtail is a lizard-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

hesperornis.name: Hesperornis
hesperornis.tamingNotice: To tame a Hesperornis, you must kill a fish, and drag the fish's corpse to the Hesperornis to feed it. The fish's size plays a major factor in how many fish will be required (a 1.0x fish appears to fill up the taming bar twice as much as a 0.5x fish). Level of fish does not appear to impact taming. The Sabertooth Salmon is by far the most effective fish, equivalent of about 4 Coels of the same size, while the Piranha is equivalent to about 2.4 Coels.
hesperornis.desc: The Hesperornis is a flightless aquatic bird.

hyaenodon.name: Hyaenodon
hyaenodon.desc: The Hyaenodon is a Hyaena-like creature.

ichthyornis.name: Ichthyornis
ichthyornis.desc: The Ichthyornis is a seagull that can be tamed to fetch fish.

iguanodon.name: Iguanodon
iguanodon.desc: The Iguanodon is a dinosaur with the unique ability to walk on either two or four legs. When walking on two, it can attack enemies with its front feet, and while walking on four, it can sprint without running out of stamina. The Iguanodon also has the ability to convert fruit and vegetables into seeds.

jerboa.name: Jerboa
jerboa.desc: While the Jerboa has little practical use, some survivors enjoy its companionship as a cuddly, shoulder-mounted pet. This mini kangaroo-like creature is able to sense upcoming weather changes and its behavior will indicate when a tribe might need to prepare. The Jerboa is easy to tame, however, low torpor means survivors need to pay close attention to it while taming.

kaprosuchus.name: Kaprosuchus
kaprosuchus.desc: The Kaprosuchus is a crocodile-like reptile commonly found around swamps. Though it is a smaller, weaker version of the Sarco, some survivors perfer it for its speed — both on land and in water.

karkinos.name: Karkinos
karkinos.tamingNotice: The Karkinos is a creature in Ark: Aberration.
karkinos.desc: The Karkinos is a massive crab-like creature in Ark: Aberration that can grab and smash creatures and players. It can also throw them at great lengths. Using its strong legs, the Karkinos can leap to impressive heights.

kentrosaurus.name: Kentrosaurus
kentrosaurus.desc: While the Kentrosaurus may appear to just be a version of the Stegosaurus, its strength should not be mistaken. With its sharp defensive spikes and deadly tail, the Kentrosaurus can even take on larger carnivores — especially when in herds. Because of its sharp spines, saddling a Kentrosaurus is not possible.

lamprey.name: Lamprey
lamprey.tamingNotice: The Lamprey can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.
lamprey.desc: The Lamprey is a leech-like creature in Aberration.

leedsichthys.name: Leedsichthys
leedsichthys.tamingNotice: The Leedsichthys cannot be tamed, however, it can be trapped so that tribes can scrape off Raw Prime Meat from its body without killing it.

liopleurodon.name: Liopleurodon
liopleurodon.desc: The Liopleurodon is a aquatic reptile often found hiding in the reefs of the ocean.

lymantria.name: Lymantria
lymantria.desc: The Lymantria is a moth-like creature that can expel a cloud of poisonous spores. While its slow flying speed make it a less suitable flying mount for transportation, survivors can use its spores to slow down enemies.

lystrosaurus.name: Lystrosaurus
lystrosaurus.desc: The Lystrosaurus is a small, common herbivore often used as a pet. While the Lystrosaurus will not fight, it can be useful to have around — or as a companion on short hunting trips — as it increases experience of nearby creatures and survivors. The Lystrosaurus must be tamed passively, making it very easy to acquire by any survivor with a handful of Rare Flowers.

manticore.name: Manticore
manticore.tamingNotice: The Manticore is a boss in Scorched Earth. Have a good strategy on how to battle Manticore? Share a tip!

megalosaurus.name: Megalosaurus
megalosaurus.desc: The megalosaurus is one of the strongest therapods, but its nocturnal sleeping pattern make it significantly less effective during the day. The megalosaurus can bite and even latch onto enemies — including humans — and swing them around, hindering their ability to move. This carnivore is stronger than a Carno or a Rex at night, but during the day, it is much more slow and sluggish.

megapithecus.name: Megapithecus
megapithecus.tamingNotice: The Megapithecus is one of the three bosses in Ark. Have a good strategy on how to battle Megapithecus? Share a tip!

microraptor.name: Microraptor
microraptor.desc: The Microraptor is a tiny, agile dinosaur with the ability to attack predators while ignoring their mounts. Its wings also give it the ability to glide after leaping.

morellatops.name: Morellatops
morellatops.desc: The Morellatops is a camel-like creature that has the ability to store water in its hump. It can be essential as a pack animal when transporting supplies through the hot, dry desert. The Morellatops will flee once attacked, but once knocked out, it is a relatively easy creature to tame.

mosasaurus.name: Mosasaurus
mosasaurus.desc: An elusive marine lizard and reputed as one of the largest creature found in the waters, the Mosasaurus is much more powerful than any known aquatic beast encountered in the depth. While its sluggish speed may put off some survivors, being ambushed by one can mean a certain death.

moschops.name: Moschops
moschops.tamingNotice: The Moschops eats Sap, Giant Bee Honey, Leech Blood, Rare Mushrooms, Rare Flowers, Organic Polymer, Raw Prime Meat, and Raw Prime Fish Meat. Each time you feed it, its desired food will change. Have a good Moschops taming technique? Share a tip!
moschops.desc: The Moschops is a omnivorous therapsid best known for its love for food. Survivors can train it to favour specific types of food — whether it be Prime Meat or Rare Flowers — and it will become more effective at gathering it. The Moschops is a very cowardly creature and will flee from any sight of danger.

nameless.name: Nameless
nameless.tamingNotice: The Nameless is an untamable creature in Ark: Aberration.
nameless.desc: The Nameless is an untamable chupacabra-like creature in Ark: Aberration. The alpha Nameless will slowly spawn other Nameless over time.

otter.name: Otter
otter.tamingNotice: To tame an otter, kill some fish, approach the otter, and then use the action button to feed the fish to it. Level of fish does not impact taming. The Sabertooth Salmon is by far the most effective fish, followed by the Piranha and the Coelacanth. Please ignore timing and effectiveness as calculations are not yet complete.

overseer.name: Overseer
overseer.tamingNotice: The Overseer is the final boss in Ark: Survival Evolved. This creature's Dododex profile may contain spoilers. Have a good strategy on how to battle The Overseer? Share a tip!

ovis.name: Ovis
ovis.desc: The ovis is a sheep-like creature that many survivors find useful in farming. It can be found in the grasslands. While rare, it can be tamed simply by feeding it one Sweet Vegetable Cake. This sheep can be sheered with Scissors to obtain Wool, or killed to obtain Mutton. While the ovis can be mounted, it is not an ideal mount for transport and provides very little use once mounted, other than its ability to climb up steep inclines.

pachyrhinosaurus.name: Pachyrhinosaurus
pachyrhinosaurus.desc: The Pachyrhinosaurus is a herbivore with a unique ability to manipulate its enemies. This cunning dinosaur can emit two types of mists that manipulates most nearby creatures to be either passive or aggressive. This allows survivors to safely travel through a dangerous area or even herd a group of vicious creatures to use against an enemy. The Pachyrhinosaurus is slightly larger than the Triceratops, and wears a two-person saddle once tamed.

pegomastax.name: Pegomastax
pegomastax.desc: The Pegomastax is a small herbivore popular among farmers. The Pegomastax has an exceptional skill of gathering seeds and berries, while also able to gather rare ingredients such as Rare Flowers and Rare Mushrooms. While it is relatively weak, this small dinosaur will become quite agressive if provoked.

pelagornis.name: Pelagornis
pelagornis.desc: The Pelagornis is a versatile pelican-like bird and the only creature able to walk, fly, and surface-swim.

phoenix.name: Phoenix
phoenix.tamingNotice: To tame a Phoenix, shoot it with a flame arrow, flamethrower or Fire Wyvern. Weapon quality impacts taming speed; a 200% damage bow will be twice as fast as a 100% bow. Please ignore taming effectiveness and taming times as the Phoenix has unique calculations. Have a good taming technique idea? Share a tip!

phiomia.name: Phiomia
phiomia.desc: While the Phiomia does not attack, many survivors see value in it as an easy-to-tame pack animal. It will quickly flee when attempting to knock it out, but once tranquilized, the Phiomia can be tamed very quickly, making it a popular choice for survivors looking for a creature to transport supplies. The Phiomia produces a lot of feces in comparison to other creatures, making it useful in fertilizer production.

piranha.name: Piranha
piranha.tamingNotice: The Piranha can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

pteranodon.name: Pteranodon
pteranodon.desc: The pteranodon is a fast and versatile flying mount useful for traveling and scouting, though not always the ideal choice for battle. Knocking a pteranodon out doesn't take much, but can still be a challenge since it will immediately flee after being attacked. Once knocked out, taming is quite easy in comparison to other creatures, and with its low saddle requirements, this makes it an especially popular creature for newer survivors while still being versatile enough for more experienced survivors. What the pterandon lacks in stamina, weight, and health, it makes up with its speed.

purlovia.name: Purlovia
purlovia.desc: The Purlovia is a mammal with the unique ability to burrow underground and hibrinate. Using the technique, the Purlovia will pounce once a predator appears nearby.

quetzal.name: Quetzal
quetzal.desc: The Quetzal is a behemoth of a creature with base stats that top the charts (health, stamina, weight, and torpor). The Quetzal's platform saddle make it an excellent choice for a mobile air base or even a caravan for transporting and gathering metal and other supplies on harder to reach areas. While its melee strength isn't as high as some might expect, its health and ability to carry weapons make it suitable to use as a war bird. Its preference for Rex Kibble make it difficult to tame, and even more so difficult to knock out in the air.

raptor.name: Raptor
raptor.desc: The Raptor is a well-rounded and easy-to-tame dinosaur. Its high speed and ability to defend itself make it very useful for travel, especially for newer survivors. While the raptor has a lower torpor tolerance, its speed can often make it difficult to target.

ravager.name: Ravager
ravager.desc: The Ravager is a tamable creature in Ark: Aberration.

reaper.name: Reaper
reaper.tamingNotice: To tame a Reaper, you must get a Reaper Queen to impregnate you. Visit the Tips section to see detailed strategies — or add your own!
reaper.desc: The Reaper King and Queen are creatures in Ark: Aberration.

rockdrake.name: Rock Drake
rockdrake.tamingNotice: The Rock Drake must be tamed like the Wyvern. To acquire one, you must steal and raise its egg.
rockdrake.desc: The Rock Drake is a gliding creature that has the ability to cloak itself and its rider. Using a Rock Drake's excellent climbing skills, survivors can traverse across steep cliffs. The Rock Drake can only be found in a particular cavern and is relatively tough to tame.

rockelemental.name: Rock Elemental
rockelemental.note: 7.5 provides a better estimate, because sometimes TE starts at 89.5%?
rockelemental.tamingNotice: To knock out a Rock Elemental, you must target its head.
rockelemental.desc: The Rock Elemental is a massive rock monster that is typically found disguised as a stone formation. When a survivor enters its territory, it will begin thrashing and throwing large boulders. Once tamed, it can be a highly effective siege weapon to bring into battle.

rollrat.name: Roll Rat
rollrat.tamingNotice: To tame a Roll Rat, wait until it burrows and underground then drop a food item into its burrow.
rollrat.desc: The Roll Rat is a tamable, rideable mole-like creature in Ark: Aberration. Almost like a more powerful Doedicurus, you can rapidly roll while mounted, plowing through enemies in its path with its spiked saddle. This advanced metal saddle can seat 6 survivors and must be repaired after repeatedly rolling.

sabertoothsalmon.name: Sabertooth Salmon
sabertoothsalmon.tamingNotice: The Sabertooth Salmon can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

seeker.name: Seeker
seeker.tamingNotice: The Seeker is an untamable creature in Ark: Aberration. Submit a tip about this creature!
seeker.desc: The Seeker is a creature in Ark: Aberration.

shinehorn.name: Shinehorn
shinehorn.tamingNotice: The Shinehorn is a creature in Ark: Aberration.
shinehorn.desc: The Shinehorn is a jackalope-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

tapejara.name: Tapejara
tapejara.desc: The Tapejara is a versatile and highly maneuverable pterosaur known for its three-person saddle. While it may not have as much stamina and weight carrying capacity as other creatures, it has unique benefits in combat. The Tapejara can land on trees and other vertical surfaces, allowing both the pilot and the passengers to use weapons. Its rudder-like fin make it the only flying creature able to hover and strafe side-to-side.

therizinosaurus.name: Therizinosaurus
therizinosaurus.desc: The Tickle Chicken (also known by its more boring, scientific name, Therizinosaurus) is a medium-sized, agressive dinosaur. While it is slow and cannot carry much weight, it is a quite versatile mount, being very strong in battle and having the ability to gather resources effectively. The Therizinosaurus can be trained to gather specific types of resources for its rider.

thylacoleo.name: Thylacoleo
thylacoleo.desc: The Thylacoleo is a large, powerful mount that can climb up trees and pounce on its enemies.

titanoboa.name: Titanoboa
titanoboa.tamingNotice: These values are egg-stracted from Dododex's own tests and user reports. Timing and intervals are rough estimates, as the Titanoboa's eating pattern is unclear. Use the 'Report Data Error' button if any of your eggs differ. The Titanoboa must be tamed with fertilized eggs. Drop an egg near it and it will consume it.

titanosaur.name: Titanosaur
titanosaur.tamingNotice: To knock out a Titanosaur, you must target its head.
titanosaur.desc: The Titanosaur is the largest creature in Ark whose stats top the charts across the board. This sauropod's massive platform saddle allows tribes to build large fortresses on its back — if they're skilled enough to tame it.

trilobite.name: Trilobite
trilobite.tamingNotice: The Trilobite can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

tusoteuthis.name: Tusoteuthis
tusoteuthis.desc: The Tusoteuthis is a massive, aggressive squid found in the depths of the oceans. In battle, the Tusoteuthis can grab its prey and knock it unconcious, siphoning its blood to gain health. Once tamed, the ink from a Tusoteuthis can be used as a constant Oil source. Some survivors choose to hunt the Tusoteuthis for its Oil.
tusoteuthis.tamingNotice: The Tusoteuthis's taming method differs from most creatures. Please ignore its interval and time calculations.

wyvern.name: Wyvern
wyvern.tamingNotice: To tame a Wyvern, survivors must steal a Wyvern egg. Once hatched, Wyvern babies need to be fed Wyvern Milk, which can be obtained by knocking out a female Wyvern.
wyvern.desc: The Wyvern is a highly sought-after massive flying dragon that can overpower most creatures it faces. The deadly Wyvern, which is only tamable by stealing and raising as a baby, can be found in three varieities — Fire, Lightning, and Poison — each of which have distinct attacks.

yeti.name: Yeti
yeti.tamingNotice: The Yeti is an Alpha creature found in the Snow Cave. It cannot be tamed.

ingredients.item: Cooked Prime Meat or Prime Meat Jerky

165.name: Cactus Broth
ef: Makes user less noticable to wild creatures

173.name: Bug Repellant
ef: Reduces agressiveness of insects and related creatures

187.name: Beer Jar
ef: Applies hangover for 1 minute after consumption, keeping stamina at 0 and preventing effects of stew

221.name: Stimulant
221.ci: Mortar And Pestle or Chemistry Bench
